yingyinNormal.en: I'm having the last cronut. I'm so depressed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要去把最后一个可颂甜甜圈吃掉，我太难过了。

yingyinNormal.en: She's reading the same book over and over. She's depressed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她会把同一本书读了又读。她有些抑郁。

yingyinNormal.en: Blue, as in depressed. Well, not so much depressed as lonely. I don't know what color lonely is.
yingyinNormal.zh: 蓝色，就是郁闷的意思。还没郁闷到孤独的地步。我不知道孤独是什么颜色。

yingyinNormal.en: Late in the winter of my seventeenth year, my mother decided that I was depressed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在我十七岁那年的深冬，我妈妈觉得我有些抑郁。

yingyinNormal.en: Look, Reche, I can sense when women are depressed and vulnerable. It's one of my gifts.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可以感觉到女人难过脆弱的时候，这是我的天赋之一。

yingyinNormal.en: What? Red is angry; yellow is frightened; green is jealous, and blue is depressed. Perhaps we can assign a color to lonely.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么？红色代表愤怒，黄色代表惊恐，绿色代表嫉妒，蓝色代表忧郁，没准咱可以找个颜色来代表孤独。

yingyinNormal.en: Elaine even said her brother was depressed, but here's the thing, according to the report, one hotel guest said that she heard loud male voices before Abel went all flying squirrel.
yingyinNormal.zh: 埃琳还说她兄弟很抑郁，但问题是，根据这份报告酒店有位客人说，当晚听到先有男性大呼小叫，然后亚伯才变身空中飞鼠。
